notes.text:
Updated git19-git packages that fix one security issue are now available
for Red Hat Software Collections 2.

Red Hat Product Security has rated this update as having Moderate security
impact. A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which
gives a detailed severity rating, is available from the CVE link in the
References section.
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
Git is a distributed revision control system with a decentralized
architecture. As opposed to centralized version control systems with a
client-server model, Git ensures that each working copy of a Git repository
is an exact copy with complete revision history. This not only allows the
user to work on and contribute to projects without the need to have
permission to push the changes to their official repositories, but also
makes it possible for the user to work with no network connection.

A flaw was found in the way the git-remote-ext helper processed certain
URLs. If a user had Git configured to automatically clone submodules from
untrusted repositories, an attacker could inject commands into the URL of a
submodule, allowing them to execute arbitrary code on the user's system.
(BZ#1269794)

All git19-git users are advised to upgrade to these updated packages, which
contain a backported patch to correct this issue.

cwe.name: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in a Command ('Command Injection')

notes.text: A flaw was found in the way the git-remote-ext helper processed certain URLs. If a user had Git configured to automatically clone submodules from untrusted repositories, an attacker could inject commands into the URL of a submodule, allowing them to execute arbitrary code on the user's system.
notes.title: Vulnerability description

notes.text: git: arbitrary code execution via crafted URLs
notes.title: Vulnerability summary

notes.text: The CVSS score(s) listed for this vulnerability do not reflect the associated product's status, and are included for informational purposes to better understand the severity of this vulnerability.
notes.title: CVSS score applicability

remediations.details:
Before applying this update, make sure all previously released errata
relevant to your system have been applied.

For details on how to apply this update, refer to:

https://access.redhat.com/articles/11258

Avoid recursive cloning or updating of git submodules without checking the submodule URL. Non-recursive cloning is the default in git, so user needs to change this to become vulnerable ("e.g. by specifying --recursive").

vulnerabilities.title: git: arbitrary code execution via crafted URLs
